cs.FL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL 

The paper deals with the problem of synthesizing string to string transformations from input/output examples using deterministic finite automata (DFA). This falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also proposes an algorithm that uses SMT solvers, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of the problem, which is related to computational complexity theory (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the synthesis of functions, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL).
